statement.tex:
\text{Find the points on the curve }y=x^3 \\
\text{at which the slope of the tangent is}\\
\text{equal to the y-coordinate of the point.}

reason.tex:
\text{Notice that }cx^2 = x^3 \text{ is true for }x = 0.\\
				\text{Which is why, one cannot simply do }\frac{x^3}{x^2} = x = c. \\
				\text{This operation makes no sense when x = 0.}
